body:
I'm unable to analyze the specific codebase at https://github.com/eonist/claude-talk-to-figma-mcp/ as the content wasn't successfully loaded from that repository[1]. However, based on similar MCP projects for Claude-Figma integration, I can suggest areas where method documentation is typically lacking and how to improve them.

## Potential Areas Needing Better Documentation

**Tool Implementation Methods**
Functions in tool modules (document-tools.ts, creation-tools.ts, etc.) often lack comprehensive parameter descriptions[[3](https://github.com/arinspunk/claude-talk-to-figma-mcp)][[4](https://github.com/arinspunk/claude-talk-to-figma-mcp)]. For example:

```typescript
// Before
function createRectangle(params) {
  // Implementation
}

// Improved
/**
 * Creates a rectangle in the Figma document
 * @param {Object} params - Configuration parameters
 * @param {number} params.x - X position of rectangle
 * @param {number} params.y - Y position of rectangle
 * @param {number} params.width - Width of rectangle
 * @param {number} params.height - Height of rectangle
 * @param {string} [params.color] - Fill color (hex format)
 * @param {number} [params.cornerRadius] - Corner radius in pixels
 * @returns {Promise} - ID of the created node
 */
function createRectangle(params) {
  // Implementation
}
```

**WebSocket Communication Methods**
WebSocket handling typically needs better error state documentation[[3](https://github.com/arinspunk/claude-talk-to-figma-mcp)]:

```typescript
// Before
function handleWebSocketMessage(message) {
  // Implementation
}

// Improved
/**
 * Processes incoming WebSocket messages from Figma plugin
 * @param {Object} message - The parsed message object
 * @param {string} message.type - Message type identifier
 * @param {string} message.channelId - Channel for communication
 * @param {Object} [message.payload] - Optional data payload
 * @throws Will throw error if message format is invalid
 */
function handleWebSocketMessage(message) {
  // Implementation
}
```

**Configuration Helper Functions**
Installation and setup methods often lack environment-specific details[[2](https://libraries.io/npm/claude-talk-to-figma-mcp)][[4](https://github.com/arinspunk/claude-talk-to-figma-mcp)]:

```typescript
// Before
function configureClaudeDesktop() {
  // Implementation
}

// Improved
/**
 * Configures Claude Desktop to use the Figma MCP
 * @description Modifies the Claude Desktop configuration file to include
 * the ClaudeTalkToFigma MCP. Creates a backup of the existing config.
 * @platform Supports macOS (~/Library/Application Support/Claude/...)
 * @platform Supports Windows (%APPDATA%\Claude\...)
 * @returns {boolean} True if configuration was successful
 */
function configureClaudeDesktop() {
  // Implementation 
}
```

These improvements would make the codebase more maintainable and easier for contributors to understand[[3](https://github.com/arinspunk/claude-talk-to-figma-mcp)].

